## Square Catalog API Configuration

# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual Square API values.
# All Square API calls are handled server-side to keep tokens secure.

# Required server-side environment variables for Square integration
SQUARE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_square_access_token_here
SQUARE_APPLICATION_ID=your_square_application_id_here
SQUARE_LOCATION_ID=your_square_location_id_here
SQUARE_ENV=production

# Optional: Discord invite used on the Game page
VITE_DISCORD_INVITE=https://discord.gg/pyEkgdDmgv

# How to get your Square credentials:
# 1. Go to your Square Developer Dashboard: https://developer.squareup.com/apps
# 2. Create a new application or select an existing one
# 3. Navigate to the "Credentials" tab in your application
# 4. Get your Access Token (starts with "EAA..." for production)
# 5. Get your Application ID (visible on the same credentials page)
# 6. Get your Location ID from Square Dashboard > Locations
# 7. Fill SQUARE_ACCESS_TOKEN with your production access token
# 8. Fill SQUARE_APPLICATION_ID with your Application ID
# 9. Fill SQUARE_LOCATION_ID with your Location ID
# 10. Set SQUARE_ENV to "sandbox" for testing or "production" for live
# 11. Restart the dev server after making changes to .env

# Security note:
# - Square Access Tokens are sensitive and should ONLY be set in server-side environment variables
# - Never expose Square tokens to the browser/client-side code
# - All Square API calls go through our /api/products endpoints for security

# Required permissions for your Square Access Token:
# - ITEMS_READ (to fetch catalog items)
# - MERCHANT_PROFILE_READ (for location details)